<HEADLINE>
FT  30 NOV 93 / Arts: Stafford-Clark bows out
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MALCOLM RUTHERFORD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Max Stafford-Clark took his formal departure from London's Royal Court
Theatre on Sunday after 14 years as artistic director, writes Malcolm
Rutherford. A packed house saw a gala performance of scenes from plays he
has put on over the years, including Serious Money by Caryl Churchill and
Three Birds Alighting on a Field by Timberlake Wertenbaker. In future,
Stafford-Clark will head a new company, Out of Joint. Its first venture will
be a co-production with the Leicester Haymarket and the Royal Court of an
adaptation of Sue Townsend's novel The Queen and I.
</TEXT>
