FT  30 NOV 93 / Business and the Law: Merger complete - Legal Briefs
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The 'merger' between Dibb Lupton Broomhead, based in Leeds and London, and
Needham &amp; James, of Birmingham and Stratford-upon-Avon, finally comes into
operation tomorrow. The merger has given Dibb Lupton the presence in the
west Midlands that it needed to further its ambitions to become the first
truly national law firm in England - a title the constituent firms of the
Eversheds group might dispute. The name of Needham &amp; James will disappear in
Birmingham.
