<TEXT>
The Democratic party in New Jersey has dropped its lawsuit seeking to
invalidate this month's election to pick the state's new governor, in which
Mrs Christine Todd Whitman, the Republican candidate, defeated incumbent
Governor Jim Florio, reports George Graham from Washington.
The suit had been filed after Mr Ed Rollins, Mrs Whitman's campaign manager,
said the campaign had paid black preachers to stop their congregations from
voting.
Mr Rollins later said under oath that he had made this up to taunt Mr
Florio's campaign manager. Democratic leaders concluded they could not prove
the Republicans paid to suppress black votes.
