</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOSEPH MANN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CARACAS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Venezuela is investigating reports that 19 members of the Yanomami tribe
died and many became seriously ill because of mercury poisoning, writes
Joseph Mann in Caracas.
They lived in a remote jungle area in Bolivar state, near the Brazilian
border. The area is frequently the scene of conflicts between illegal gold
miners from Brazil and the Yanomami, who have communities on both sides of
the border. Earlier this year, miners massacred Yanomami in another border
area.
